LAGOS – The market women at Kudaki Ul­tra-Modern Market in Ikotun-Egbe area of Lagos State were celebrated as Inner Wheel District 912 Nigeria marked the International Women’s Day with a visit to the market where different foods as well as clothing, shoes and other items were shared to both men and women. In a well-attended ceremony where more than 200 of the women and men received various items to mark the day, the Chairman of Inner Wheel District 912 Nigeria, IWM Adefunke Olubunmi Shinaba, said women hold special place in the hearts of Inner Wheel District 912 members, hence the visit. Shinaba noted that it was impera­tive that women rose to the challenge of motherhood, saying the place of women cannot be over-emphasised, saying since her tenure, more than 40 women had been empowered through various skills. Amotekun Bursts International Human Trafficking, Kidnap… Suspected Cultists Cut Off Man’s Head In Bayelsa “It is very valuable to be a wom­an. Today in the whole world, Inter­national Women’s Day is being cele­brated and Inner Wheel all over the world is celebrating women. “Today we come here to empower about 250 women and men with var­ious food items and other things as part of our own way of celebrating today.”